  section
    h3.red Rounding trouble
    p An online shop is processing orders.
    p Suddenly all coins worth less than one dollar are abolished!
    p How should the shop round each item price
    p so that every order total changes only a little?
  section
    p 
      span Suppose the items are $1, 2, \dots, n$
      span.fragment , and the fractional part of item $i$ is $c_i$
    p.fragment Orders $S_1, \dots, S_m \subset \{1, 2, \dots, n\}$
    h3.red.fragment Beck-Fiala theorem
    p.fragment If each $i$ appears in at most $d$ sets $S_k$,
    p.fragment then there are $z_1, \dots, z_n \in \{0,1\}$
    p.fragment such that $\left|\sum_{i \in S_k} z_i - \sum_{i \in S_k}c_i\right| < d$ for every $S_k$.
  section
    p.red.fragment Let the prices move?
    p.fragment $c_i \in (0,1) \to x_i \in [0,1] \to z_i \in \{0,1\}$
    p.fragment Rule: once $x_i$ reaches 0 or 1, it stays fixed
    p.fragment Before it is fixed, we say $x_i$ is floating
    p.red.fragment While prices are floating, which $S_k$ should worry us?
    p.fragment Call an order dangerous if it contains more than $d$ floating items
    p.fragment Fewer and fewer items float, so fewer and fewer orders are dangerous
  section
    p.red.fragment How can prices move while every dangerous order total stays fixed?
    p.fragment Dangerous orders $\Leftrightarrow$ linear constraints on the floating prices $x_i$
    p.fragment Number of constraints $<$ number of floating prices?
    p.fragment Nonzero solution $\implies$ floating prices can move at constant velocity
    p.fragment until some floating price first reaches 0 or 1
    p.fragment
      span After an order stops being dangerous,
      br
      span its at most $d$ floating items can change the total by $< d$.
  section
    h3.red Discrepancy theory
    p.fragment $S_1, \dots, S_m \subset \{1,2,\dots, n\}$
    p.fragment Given a coloring $f\colon \{1,2,\dots, n\} \to \{-1, 1\}$
    p.fragment Score it by $\chi(f) = \max_k |\sum_{i\in S_k}f(i)|$
    p.fragment If each $i$ appears in at most $d$ sets $S_k$,
    p.fragment how large can $\min_f\chi(f)$ be?
  section
